%% RHOAI 3.5-ea.2 — Workflow 3: MaaS External Provider Routing
%% Generated from PLATFORM.md by Claude Opus 4.6 on 2026-06-22

sequenceDiagram
    participant Admin as Platform Admin
    participant MaaSCtrl as MaaS Controller<br/>Reconciler
    participant K8s as Kubernetes API<br/>CRDs + Secrets
    participant Gateway as Platform Gateway<br/>Envoy
    participant ExtProc as ext_proc Pipeline<br/>ai-gateway-payload-processing
    participant Authorino as Kuadrant Authorino<br/>Auth Enforcement
    participant User as API Client
    participant Provider as External LLM Provider<br/>OpenAI / Anthropic

    Note over Admin,Provider: Workflow 3 — MaaS External Provider Routing

    %% Step 1: Admin configures provider
    Admin->>K8s: Create ExternalProvider CR<br/>(endpoint URL, credential Secret)
    Admin->>K8s: Create ExternalModel CR<br/>(maps model name to provider)
    Admin->>K8s: Create Secret with provider API key<br/>(SHA-256 hashed for storage)

    %% Step 2: MaaS controller reconciles
    MaaSCtrl->>K8s: Watch ExternalProvider + ExternalModel CRs
    K8s-->>MaaSCtrl: New resources detected
    MaaSCtrl->>K8s: Create ExternalName Service<br/>(points to provider endpoint)
    MaaSCtrl->>K8s: Create Istio ServiceEntry<br/>(allows egress to provider)
    MaaSCtrl->>K8s: Create HTTPRoute<br/>(model-level routing through Gateway)
    MaaSCtrl->>K8s: Create AuthPolicy<br/>(API Key + TokenReview validation)

    Note over Gateway,ExtProc: Gateway configured — model routable

    %% Step 3: User sends inference request
    User->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>model: gpt-4-turbo<br/>API Key: sk-oai-...<br/>(HTTPS TLS 1.3)

    %% Step 4: Auth and pre-processing
    Gateway->>Authorino: Validate API Key<br/>(SHA-256 hash comparison,<br/>constant-time, fail-closed)
    Authorino-->>Gateway: Auth OK

    Gateway->>ExtProc: ext_proc pre-auth stage<br/>Extract model name from<br/>request body into HTTP header
    ExtProc-->>Gateway: Model header added<br/>(for HTTPRoute matching)

    Gateway->>Gateway: Route request via HTTPRoute<br/>(match on model header)

    Gateway->>ExtProc: ext_proc post-auth stage
    ExtProc->>ExtProc: Translate API format<br/>(if provider uses different schema)
    ExtProc->>K8s: Read provider API key<br/>from Kubernetes Secret
    K8s-->>ExtProc: Provider API key
    ExtProc->>ExtProc: Inject provider API key<br/>into outbound request headers
    ExtProc-->>Gateway: Transformed request ready

    %% Step 5: Forward to external provider
    Gateway->>Provider: Forward request<br/>(HTTPS TLS 1.2+, provider API key,<br/>via ServiceEntry + ExternalName)
    Provider->>Provider: Run LLM inference
    Provider-->>Gateway: Inference response

    %% Step 6: Response processing
    Gateway->>ExtProc: ext_proc response stage<br/>(format translation if needed)
    ExtProc-->>Gateway: Translated response
    Gateway-->>User: JSON response<br/>(OpenAI-compatible format,<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.3)
